  "body": "Following #2144  \r\n\r\nOnce the appearance setting is global, next step is to set the default of this global setting to 'system default' when the app is launched for the first time\r\n\r\nThis is likely already the case on Mac, but showed to be more difficult on Windows. As part of this issue it would be good to verify the current behavior on Mac and Linux for any changes required.\r\n\r\n\r\n**User story** \r\nAs a user who is new to Status\r\nI want for the application to respect my system Language and Display settings on launch (account creation/import)\r\nBecause these are settings I prefer for my applications\r\n\r\nRelated discussion: https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/discussions/2145",
